name: ENS: Ethereum Name Service
description: Ethereum Name Service (ENS) domains are secure domain names for the decentralized world. ENS domains provide a way for users to map human readable names to blockchain and non-blockchain resources, like Ethereum addresses, IPFS hashes, or website URLs. ENS domains can be bought and sold on secondary markets.

name: Murakami.Flowers Official
description:
Murakami.Flowers is a work in which artist Takashi Murakami’s representative artwork, flowers, are expressed as dot art evocative of Japanese TV games created in the 1970s. The work is being developed with the number 108 as the keyword; a combination of 108 backgrounds and flower colors make up a field, and there are 108 fields. Each field has 108 flower images, resulting in 11,664 flower images in total. The number 108 is a reference to bonnō, or earthly temptations.

Murakami.Flowers NFTs are subject to the Collector Terms available here: https://murakamiflowers.kaikaikiki.com/collector.html. If you buy a Murakami.Flowers NFT, you do not receive commercial rights in the corresponding artwork.

©Takashi Murakami/Kaikai Kiki Co., Ltd. All Rights Reserved.

name: [ Ledger ] Market Pass - Genesis Edition
description:
[ Ledger ] Market is the most secure platform for artists and brands to release their NFTs, where Ledger customers can securely connect through Ledger Live and clear sign their transactions. For first access to exclusive collaborations, and Ledger hardware, software and services, become a [ Ledger ] Market Pass holder.


[ L ] Market’s brand mark is a generative font with over two billion unique variations. It speaks to: 1) the massive awareness generative art and PFP projects have brought to blockchain technology, and 2) the advanced cryptography built into Ledger and [ Ledger ] Market’s DNA.

name: COVIDPunks!
description:
"It's punk to wear a mask!"

COVIDPunks are 10,000 parody Punks raising awareness about COVID protocols. Mask up and get vaccinated! We're all in this together. 

The project donated to CARE, a global humanitarian relief fund that aims to save lives and reduce poverty. CARE's current mission includes COVID relief in those places most devastated by the pandemic. 

NOTE: This is *not* a Larva Labs project. We love LL and their contribution to this space. They have inspired many, and helped democratize art for the masses.
